    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-14T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-14T09:00:00-05:00" n="204"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d204">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.M2/–: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-14T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1927—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 14—1:54 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Council today adopted Stresemann report fixing date Diplomatic Conference
                    Abolition Export and Import Prohibitions [and] Restrictions for October 17,
                    1927. This date chosen in order not to conflict with proposed meeting
                    Preparatory Commission for Disarmament in November.<note n="89"
                        xml:id="d204fn89">For correspondence concerning the fourth session of the
                        Preparatory Commission, see p<ref target="#pg_159">p. 159</ref> ff.</note>
                    Report calls attention of states invited to Conference to conclusion[s]
                    formulated by International Economic Conference<note n="90" xml:id="d204fn90"
                        >See <ref target="#pg_238">pp. 238</ref> ff.</note> on the subject [of]
                    prohibitions. All countries who sent delegations to Economic Conference will
                    receive invitation to attend.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tuck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
